<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Seasonally dry mountainous regions from the United States Southwest through Mexico and Central America to Peru, occurring mostly from 500-2000 m often at somewhat lower altitudes than 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="plummerae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea plummerae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is very sporadic in South America.
</paragraph>
